1
00:00:00,792 --> 00:00:02,752
[AREZA]<i> We'll go to the blast site.</i>
<i>We'll go through here.</i>

2
00:00:02,836 --> 00:00:04,629
<i>- Hardly anyone passes through there.</i>
- [AREZA] <i>Exactly.</i>

3
00:00:04,713 --> 00:00:07,799
<i>It's likely they didn't plant traps there</i>
<i>because no one uses that path.</i>

4
00:00:07,882 --> 00:00:10,552
- [MIKE] <i>All right.</i>
<i>- Let's go this way.</i>

5
00:00:10,635 --> 00:00:11,928
<i>Come on.</i>

6
00:00:12,011 --> 00:00:13,680
[DADO]<i> We're planting bombs now</i>
<i>at the main beach.</i>

7
00:00:13,763 --> 00:00:15,432
<i>If anyone goes there, boom!</i>

8
00:00:15,515 --> 00:00:17,559
<i>Wait! There are bombs there!</i>

9
00:00:17,642 --> 00:00:18,560
<i>Are you sure?</i>

10
00:00:18,643 --> 00:00:19,519
<i>Then stay here!</i>

11
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:21,604
[EXPLOSION]

12
00:00:23,189 --> 00:00:24,733
<i>- Hey, wait!</i>
<i>- What are you doing?!</i>

13
00:00:24,816 --> 00:00:25,817
<i>Those are VIPs!</i>

14
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:26,818
[DADO]<i> Then go after them.</i>

15
00:00:27,610 --> 00:00:29,279
<i>You're really going to run, huh?</i>

16
00:00:29,362 --> 00:00:33,324
[GOON]<i> The boss said</i>
<i>to get rid of anyone who's no use to us.</i>

17
00:00:33,408 --> 00:00:34,576
<i>Are you okay?</i>

18
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:37,287
[IAN] <i>We need to move.</i>
<i>They're everywhere.</i>

19
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:39,330
<i>- I got this!</i>
<i>- Run!</i>

20
00:00:39,914 --> 00:00:43,001
[GUNSHOTS]

21
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:45,253
[BOTH GRUNTING]

22
00:00:45,336 --> 00:00:48,131
[GUNSHOTS]

23
00:00:48,214 --> 00:00:50,091
[LUNA] <i>Liam! Come on!</i>

24
00:00:51,217 --> 00:00:53,303
- [BOGS]<i> Where are you taking us?!</i>
- [ICE] <i>Just trust me, Bogs!</i>

25
00:00:53,386 --> 00:00:54,304
[GOON] <i>Get rid of them.</i>

26
00:00:54,387 --> 00:00:56,514
- [BOGS, GUESTS] <i>No!</i>
- [GOON GROANS]

27
00:00:56,598 --> 00:00:58,266
[GUNSHOTS]

28
00:00:58,349 --> 00:01:00,268
- [AREZA] <i>Secure the area!</i>
- [OFFICER] <i>Yes, sir!</i>

29
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:04,564
- [OLSEN GRUNTS]
<i>- Don't! He's on our side.</i>

30
00:01:04,647 --> 00:01:07,484
<i>If I find out this is a trap,</i>
<i>you'll be the first one to blow up.</i>

31
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:08,860
<i>Do you understand?</i>

32
00:01:08,943 --> 00:01:09,819
<i>Move!</i>

33
00:01:10,695 --> 00:01:13,698
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [WOMEN SCREAMING]

34
00:01:13,782 --> 00:01:16,367
- [LUNA]<i> Run!</i>
- [STAFF WHIMPERING]

35
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:24,250
- [LIAM BREATHING HEAVILY] Stay with us.
- [STAFF WHIMPERING]

36
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:25,710
Love, hold on.

37
00:01:25,794 --> 00:01:26,753
We're here.

38
00:01:26,836 --> 00:01:28,838
- [LOVE GASPING]
- [STAFF] Love!

39
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:31,716
- [STAFF CRYING] Love!
- [LIAM] You're okay.

40
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:34,511
[LOVE GASPING, MURMURING]
W-Where are we?

41
00:01:35,094 --> 00:01:36,679
[SMILE] Love?

42
00:01:37,263 --> 00:01:39,307
- [JOY] Love…
- [LOVE CRYING] Sir.

43
00:01:40,266 --> 00:01:42,977
Sir, I don't want to die.

44
00:01:43,061 --> 00:01:44,979
You're not going to die!

45
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:48,233
We'll help you, Love!
Stay with us, Love! Stay with us!

46
00:01:48,316 --> 00:01:49,984
- Love.
- [LOVE COUGHING]

47
00:01:50,068 --> 00:01:51,611
[GASPING]

48
00:01:51,694 --> 00:01:55,323
- Love, no! Please, Love! I'm sorry.
- [LIAM] Love, stay with us!

49
00:01:55,406 --> 00:01:56,908
- [STAFF CRYING]
- [JOY] Love.

50
00:01:56,991 --> 00:01:58,243
[MURMURS] I don't want to…

51
00:01:58,326 --> 00:02:00,120
- Love!
- [LOVE COUGHING]

52
00:02:00,203 --> 00:02:02,539
[STAFF CRYING]

53
00:02:04,207 --> 00:02:05,166
[LUNA] Love?

54
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:07,252
- Love?
- [JOY] Love?

55
00:02:07,335 --> 00:02:08,628
Love!

56
00:02:08,711 --> 00:02:11,548
[BAWLING]

57
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:17,303
[JOY] Love.

58
00:02:22,976 --> 00:02:29,858
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

59
00:02:37,699 --> 00:02:39,075
Love…

60
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:40,743
[SOBBING]

61
00:02:42,745 --> 00:02:49,377
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

62
00:02:50,587 --> 00:02:52,338
[ANGUISHED SCREAM]

63
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:57,802
This is because of your betrayal!

64
00:02:59,053 --> 00:03:01,055
Whoever you are, you're a monster!

65
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:05,018
Her life!

66
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:08,146
The lives of your friends!

67
00:03:08,813 --> 00:03:12,275
Innocent people lost their lives
because of your filth!

68
00:03:13,401 --> 00:03:16,154
[STAFF CRYING]

69
00:03:16,738 --> 00:03:18,489
[LIAM] Whoever the traitor is…

70
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,037
you have no conscience.

71
00:03:25,496 --> 00:03:26,706
You're evil.

72
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:30,126
[HAPPY SOBBING]

73
00:03:33,004 --> 00:03:36,382
Your hands are stained with blood
because of what you did!

74
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:39,677
[MOURNFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

75
00:03:39,761 --> 00:03:42,639
[STAFF SOBBING SOFTLY]

76
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:44,724
[HAPPY SNIFFLES]

77
00:03:44,807 --> 00:03:46,643
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

78
00:03:46,726 --> 00:03:47,727
Liam.

79
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:50,813
There's nothing we can do now.

80
00:03:51,481 --> 00:03:52,440
[SNIFFLES]

81
00:03:52,523 --> 00:03:53,775
No.

82
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:57,820
- We can do something.
- [MUSIC STOPS]

83
00:03:57,904 --> 00:04:00,823
- [HAPPY SNIFFLES]
- I'm going to find that traitor.

84
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:06,120
I will make sure that they pay.

85
00:04:06,204 --> 00:04:13,002
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

86
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:24,013
You better watch out!

87
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:27,809
[SOBBING, SNIFFLING CONTINUES]

88
00:04:31,813 --> 00:04:34,065
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

89
00:04:34,148 --> 00:04:35,358
[SNIFFLES]

90
00:04:38,236 --> 00:04:43,324
- [SOBBING CONTINUES]
- [EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

91
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:46,411
[STAFF SNIFFLING]

92
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:54,002
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

93
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:00,967
[SCREAMS]

94
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:07,557
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

95
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:10,893
[TENSE MUSIC STING]

96
00:05:15,398 --> 00:05:21,946
- [EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [SOBBING, SNIFFLING CONTINUE]

97
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,906
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

98
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:26,993
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

99
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:45,720
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

100
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:18,377
Another bomb went off.

101
00:06:19,378 --> 00:06:22,256
I'm worried. I'm worried about Olsen.

102
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:25,426
Oh God. Oh God.

103
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:27,178
- Stay here.
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

104
00:06:27,261 --> 00:06:28,346
Why?

105
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:31,474
I'll go outside
and find out what's going on.

106
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:34,352
Magnus…

107
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:37,396
please take care.

108
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:41,692
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

109
00:06:41,776 --> 00:06:43,486
Magnus!

110
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:45,154
Where is he going?

111
00:06:46,030 --> 00:06:48,866
He said he's going to find out
what's happening out there.

112
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:52,537
Greta, stay here! It's dangerous!

113
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:54,789
Aren't you the real danger here?

114
00:06:54,872 --> 00:06:56,541
[MUSIC FADES]

115
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:07,802
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

116
00:07:11,055 --> 00:07:12,348
[WENDY] Papa! [BREATHES SHARPLY]

117
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:15,226
Men, bring the survivors inside.

118
00:07:15,309 --> 00:07:16,561
Papa!

119
00:07:16,644 --> 00:07:18,020
- Help me.
- All right.

120
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:19,105
Help me.

121
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:21,899
Assist them.

122
00:07:21,983 --> 00:07:28,114
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

123
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:47,049
So far, Police Lieutenant Areza
has already secured some of the hostages.

124
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:50,720
But I underestimated the hostage takers.

125
00:07:51,846 --> 00:07:53,097
Unfortunately,

126
00:07:53,181 --> 00:07:58,352
his team suffered some casualties.

127
00:07:58,436 --> 00:08:00,897
If that's the case, sir,
let's proceed to Plan B?

128
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:02,940
No! No, no, no, no.

129
00:08:03,024 --> 00:08:04,108
Plan B?!

130
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:08,237
Plan B is just providing backup

131
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:11,824
from our own precinct here in Alicante.

132
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:15,286
That's not enough. We need more men!

133
00:08:16,704 --> 00:08:18,247
We need more weapons!

134
00:08:19,290 --> 00:08:24,337
I will request reinforcements
from main headquarters.

135
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:26,756
[LINE RINGING]

136
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:28,007
Yes.

137
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:30,510
Can I speak to the Colonel?

138
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:32,678
- So stubborn!
- [GRUNTS]

139
00:08:34,597 --> 00:08:38,184
Boss, looks like we don't have
a problem anymore.

140
00:08:38,935 --> 00:08:40,311
The cops already blew up.

141
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:42,355
I'm sure

142
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:46,776
they're not the only police officers
who came here.

143
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:51,531
Maybe they followed your orders, boss?

144
00:08:52,156 --> 00:08:54,367
Maybe they're heading back to Alicante?

145
00:08:54,450 --> 00:08:57,537
Possibly yes, possibly no.

146
00:08:57,620 --> 00:08:59,163
But what I'm sure of

147
00:09:00,498 --> 00:09:02,792
is that nothing will stop our plans.

148
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:05,419
Sir.

149
00:09:06,629 --> 00:09:07,755
What's our plan for him?

150
00:09:10,132 --> 00:09:11,634
Let's bring him to the HQ.

151
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:16,264
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

152
00:09:18,432 --> 00:09:19,767
[GRUNTING]

153
00:09:23,813 --> 00:09:27,483
Stay there! There!
Just sit there. Sit.

154
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:28,568
I said sit there.

155
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:32,113
Take a seat here.

156
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:33,155
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

157
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:34,282
Thank you.

158
00:09:34,365 --> 00:09:36,617
Let Minnie rest for a moment.

159
00:09:37,326 --> 00:09:38,578
She can't handle it anymore.

160
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:41,831
[EXHALES]

161
00:09:41,914 --> 00:09:44,792
This was our staff house
when the resort was still being built.

162
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:46,294
Yeah, right.

163
00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:48,087
Is this it?

164
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:52,341
Bro, we need to move.
We're not safe here--

165
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:53,509
Didn't I tell you--

166
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:55,720
- I told you not to move.
- [MIKE] Olsen.

167
00:09:55,803 --> 00:09:57,555
Didn't I tell you to keep quiet?!

168
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:01,100
[MIKE] Olsen.

169
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:03,644
Give me that!

170
00:10:09,233 --> 00:10:11,110
[GUN THUDS]

171
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:16,240
[OBJECTS CLATTER]

172
00:10:16,324 --> 00:10:17,450
[BAG THUDS]

173
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:25,666
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

174
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:28,294
- What's your real name, huh?!
- [GUN CLICKS]

175
00:10:28,377 --> 00:10:29,754
What's your real name?

176
00:10:29,837 --> 00:10:31,213
Ian.

177
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,467
Ian Menor.

178
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:36,552
Are you messing with me?

179
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:38,929
You're Olsen Bonifacio?

180
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:43,267
I'll help you.

181
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:45,895
Please, believe me. I'll help all of you.

182
00:10:48,189 --> 00:10:49,315
Why?

183
00:10:50,024 --> 00:10:51,984
Why would you help us?

184
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:54,278
- Why should I trust you?
- Olsen.

185
00:10:55,488 --> 00:10:58,032
I didn't know it would come to this.

186
00:10:58,115 --> 00:10:59,367
Not in this way.

187
00:11:02,036 --> 00:11:02,953
Olsen.

188
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:06,832
Let him be.

189
00:11:13,297 --> 00:11:15,591
Thank you for helping us.

190
00:11:23,224 --> 00:11:26,310
Ma'am, the doctor said
you should take this medicine.

191
00:11:26,394 --> 00:11:28,187
Hon-- Oh.

192
00:11:28,270 --> 00:11:31,023
- I'll do it, nurse. Yeah.
- Oh. Okay, sir.

193
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:32,691
Thank you. Thank you.

194
00:11:32,775 --> 00:11:33,818
Hon…

195
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:36,821
[DOOR CLOSES]

196
00:11:36,904 --> 00:11:39,198
Um…

197
00:11:39,281 --> 00:11:40,491
You know what?

198
00:11:42,326 --> 00:11:46,288
I really didn't think
our family could be whole again.

199
00:11:48,082 --> 00:11:51,544
You still expect us to stay a family?

200
00:11:55,423 --> 00:11:56,424
Hon…

201
00:11:57,716 --> 00:12:00,302
I'm asking you for one more chance.

202
00:12:01,595 --> 00:12:02,930
Tell me, Jessie.

203
00:12:04,515 --> 00:12:07,268
If Claire were still here, alive,

204
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:10,896
would you be with me today?

205
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:12,815
I was wrong--

206
00:12:12,898 --> 00:12:14,650
I was wrong.

207
00:12:15,359 --> 00:12:17,319
I loved the wrong person.

208
00:12:19,530 --> 00:12:21,824
Your mistake, Jessie,

209
00:12:22,616 --> 00:12:25,786
was not loving the wrong person.

210
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:30,166
It was loving someone else at all.

211
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:36,547
Do you still not forgive me?

212
00:12:38,507 --> 00:12:39,592
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

213
00:12:39,675 --> 00:12:41,385
I already have.

214
00:12:43,345 --> 00:12:46,348
But that doesn't mean

215
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:47,933
I've forgotten.

216
00:12:49,768 --> 00:12:52,146
That doesn't mean

217
00:12:52,229 --> 00:12:59,028
I'm ready to go back to my life with you.

218
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:09,163
I'm deeply indebted to you.

219
00:13:09,246 --> 00:13:10,789
I owe you my life.

220
00:13:14,210 --> 00:13:16,754
I will never forget that.

221
00:13:18,797 --> 00:13:21,258
But I also won't forget…

222
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:25,971
that once, in our life
as husband and wife…

223
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:30,017
you decided…

224
00:13:30,976 --> 00:13:32,311
to leave me.

225
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:41,904
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

226
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:06,303
[OLSEN] What's this?

227
00:14:06,387 --> 00:14:11,475
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

228
00:14:12,643 --> 00:14:13,978
[MIKE] Let me see.

229
00:14:15,813 --> 00:14:17,356
Hon, didn't you make this?

230
00:14:18,566 --> 00:14:23,237
It's the final draft for La Playa Roja's
architectural blueprint.

231
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:27,074
This was supposed to be
for the renovation,

232
00:14:27,157 --> 00:14:29,493
but Ma'am Greta ordered it stopped.

233
00:14:29,577 --> 00:14:32,121
And this is the only copy.

234
00:14:33,205 --> 00:14:34,707
How do you know?

235
00:14:34,790 --> 00:14:40,087
Engineer Mike is the contractor
and engineer for La Playa Roja.

236
00:14:41,839 --> 00:14:44,925
Ms. Minnie's the architect.
You know that, right?

237
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:46,969
[CLEARS THROAT]

238
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:48,137
Wait.

239
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:52,141
There was only one copy.

240
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:54,810
How did this end up with you?

241
00:14:55,853 --> 00:14:59,106
Mike was the only person I gave that to.

242
00:14:59,189 --> 00:15:00,816
So how did you get it?

243
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:05,529
- [IAN] Oh, um…
- They're asking, Ian. Answer.

244
00:15:05,613 --> 00:15:07,615
Maybe it was stolen
from Sir Magnus's office.

245
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:11,076
I don't know. I just took it.
I'm sorry, I really don't know anything.

246
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,537
- You don't know?
- [IAN] I don't know!

247
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:15,706
- [OLSEN] Who's helping you?
- I don't know!

248
00:15:15,789 --> 00:15:17,708
- [OLSEN] Who?!
- I don't know!

249
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:20,920
[IAN] Olsen, I don't know, okay?!
Maybe it was stolen.

250
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:24,006
I just grabbed it. They probably
took it from Magnus's office.

251
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:25,799
- You don't want to talk?!
- I don't know!

252
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:27,927
- Shut up! Huh!
- [MINNIE] Olsen.

253
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:29,261
- You're not gonna talk?!
- [IAN] I don't know!

254
00:15:29,345 --> 00:15:34,058
- Olsen!
- If you won't say who, then talk! Hmm?

255
00:15:34,141 --> 00:15:36,352
- Tell me! You bastard!
- [IAN] I don't know anything!

256
00:15:36,435 --> 00:15:37,561
- I don't know!
- [MINNIE] Stop!

257
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:39,438
- [IAN] Olsen!
- Olsen, relax. Please.

258
00:15:39,521 --> 00:15:43,233
My mother was gone for ten years!

259
00:15:44,234 --> 00:15:46,445
She risked her life to save mine.

260
00:15:47,237 --> 00:15:49,198
I just saw her again.

261
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:54,787
I just got her back. Do you have
any idea what that feels like?!

262
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:56,372
[OLSEN] Huh, Ian?!

263
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:58,082
No, right?!

264
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,334
Do you know what you've done?

265
00:16:00,417 --> 00:16:02,878
- Please, I'm telling the truth!
- The hell you are!

266
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:04,630
- I really don't know, Olsen--
- [BLOW LANDS]

267
00:16:04,713 --> 00:16:06,006
- [OLSEN] Huh?!
- Olsen! Stop!

268
00:16:06,090 --> 00:16:08,258
- I swear I don't know!
- [BLOW LANDS]

269
00:16:08,342 --> 00:16:10,761
- Olsen!
- Talk!

270
00:16:10,844 --> 00:16:12,596
- I don't know!
- Talk!

271
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:15,349
[IAN'S VOICE BREAKS]
I said I don't know! I don't know, Olsen!

272
00:16:15,432 --> 00:16:17,935
- Please believe me!
- Nothing? Nothing? You bastard!

273
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:20,479
[TREMBLING VOICE] I don't know.

274
00:16:20,562 --> 00:16:21,981
Please stop.

275
00:16:22,064 --> 00:16:23,273
I don't know how it happened.

276
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:25,943
I really don't know.
Please don't kill me. I don't know!

277
00:16:26,026 --> 00:16:27,236
- You're useless!
- Olsen!

278
00:16:27,319 --> 00:16:28,570
- I don't know!
- You idiot!

279
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:29,780
- You don't know?!
- Olsen!

280
00:16:29,863 --> 00:16:31,240
[IAN] Please! Please!

281
00:16:32,449 --> 00:16:33,450
Olsen!

282
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:36,078
[CRYING, SHAKY BREATHS]

283
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:42,251
[GASPS IN RELIEF]

284
00:16:42,334 --> 00:16:43,961
[LOCKER DOOR THUDS]

285
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:47,965
[BROODING MUSIC PLAYING]

286
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:50,300
[IAN MUTTERING] Don't hurt me, please.

287
00:16:53,804 --> 00:16:55,180
How's your wound?

288
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:58,559
It's fine.

289
00:17:01,228 --> 00:17:03,480
You look deep in thought again.

290
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:09,695
Your son's smart, Wendy.

291
00:17:09,778 --> 00:17:11,155
You have to trust him.

292
00:17:13,657 --> 00:17:14,950
Papa…

293
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:19,872
I know you were one of the people
who trained Olsen.

294
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:23,417
But you can't blame me for worrying.

295
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:27,004
I don't want anything to happen to my son.

296
00:17:27,087 --> 00:17:30,299
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

297
00:17:30,382 --> 00:17:31,925
Why are you thinking like that?

298
00:17:34,928 --> 00:17:35,804
Papa…

299
00:17:37,097 --> 00:17:39,641
I just got out of prison.

300
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:43,771
This is my opportunity
to make things right with Olsen.

301
00:17:43,854 --> 00:17:46,190
We finally have a chance
to be a family again.

302
00:17:46,273 --> 00:17:48,776
You, me, and Olsen.

303
00:17:48,859 --> 00:17:52,071
[SNIFFLING, INHALES SHARPLY]

304
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:54,698
We'll get through this.

305
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:57,576
You just have to believe.

306
00:17:57,659 --> 00:17:59,536
[SNIFFLES]

307
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:02,081
And I promise you,

308
00:18:02,164 --> 00:18:04,917
we're getting out of here alive.

309
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:08,337
You, me, and Olsen.

310
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,548
[BEN] A complete family.

311
00:18:11,632 --> 00:18:13,300
Come here.

312
00:18:13,383 --> 00:18:15,260
- [SNIFFLES]
- One whole family.

313
00:18:15,344 --> 00:18:17,012
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

314
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:24,311
Here, sir.

315
00:18:28,148 --> 00:18:34,905
The suspect's description matches
what Ronaldo Chan stated in his testimony.

316
00:18:34,988 --> 00:18:41,829
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:18:44,414 --> 00:18:45,999
Is this correct?

318
00:18:48,710 --> 00:18:52,589
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

319
00:18:52,673 --> 00:18:54,091
One, two, run!

320
00:18:56,301 --> 00:19:01,431
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [PEOPLE CLAMORING]

321
00:19:03,183 --> 00:19:04,434
[SOBBING]

322
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:06,019
Get rid of him!

323
00:19:06,770 --> 00:19:07,646
Well?

324
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:09,815
Are you going to dance now?

325
00:19:14,111 --> 00:19:17,281
His eyes are rounder.

326
00:19:17,364 --> 00:19:19,116
Make them bigger.

327
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:22,870
Did you hear his name?

328
00:19:22,953 --> 00:19:25,205
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

329
00:19:25,289 --> 00:19:26,373
Uh…

330
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:30,210
<i>Uno, I talked to the president.</i>

331
00:19:30,294 --> 00:19:32,754
<i>The police haven't been notified.</i>

332
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:34,631
<i>Your plan was effective.</i>

333
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:38,552
They called him "Uno."

334
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:40,971
"Uno?"

335
00:19:41,555 --> 00:19:43,307
That's how they called each other.

336
00:19:43,390 --> 00:19:46,518
Uno, Dos, Tres.

337
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:48,770
If they called him Uno,

338
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:51,857
he must be the leader.

339
00:19:54,151 --> 00:19:55,819
I think so too, sir.

340
00:19:56,653 --> 00:19:58,071
But--[SNIFFLES]

341
00:19:58,780 --> 00:19:59,823
I'm sorry, sir.

342
00:20:00,449 --> 00:20:03,827
I can't remember what the other
hostage takers looked like anymore.

343
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:08,248
But I'm doing my best to recall, sir.

344
00:20:09,541 --> 00:20:12,002
Thank you for your cooperation, Jules.

345
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:15,797
This is for my friends

346
00:20:16,924 --> 00:20:18,759
and everyone else left there.

347
00:20:21,053 --> 00:20:23,138
Have there been any updates about them?

348
00:20:25,182 --> 00:20:29,269
We haven't had any contact with
the people at La Playa Roja.

349
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:32,022
But I can assure you,

350
00:20:32,898 --> 00:20:36,526
we're doing our best to save them.

351
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:38,570
[HOPEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

352
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:40,197
Thank you, sir.

353
00:20:43,617 --> 00:20:50,624
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

354
00:21:01,009 --> 00:21:03,762
[LUNA PANTING]

355
00:21:05,889 --> 00:21:07,057
Dude.

356
00:21:07,975 --> 00:21:09,643
I checked the perimeter.

357
00:21:09,726 --> 00:21:11,103
I think we're safe here.

358
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:14,481
We're not safe
while the traitor is still here.

359
00:21:14,564 --> 00:21:15,649
You know that.

360
00:21:15,732 --> 00:21:22,239
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

361
00:21:26,285 --> 00:21:27,661
[HAPPY] <i>What are you looking for?</i>

362
00:21:29,246 --> 00:21:30,414
<i>Sir?</i>

363
00:21:31,623 --> 00:21:32,874
<i>One of you</i>

364
00:21:34,042 --> 00:21:35,669
<i>is in cahoots with those demons.</i>

365
00:21:36,378 --> 00:21:37,462
<i>- What?</i>
<i>- What?</i>

366
00:21:38,588 --> 00:21:42,467
<i>Mrs. Roja didn't let you get an advance.</i>

367
00:21:42,551 --> 00:21:44,219
<i>Did you do this because of that?!</i>

368
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:45,971
[LOVE] <i>What about you?</i>

369
00:21:46,054 --> 00:21:49,057
<i>Didn't Ma'am Greta scold you</i>
<i>because you're slow?</i>

370
00:21:49,141 --> 00:21:50,809
<i>Ouch! You're crossing the line!</i>

371
00:21:50,892 --> 00:21:54,187
<i>- You've been like that all day!</i>
- [LIAM] <i>Stop it!</i>

372
00:21:57,524 --> 00:22:03,947
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

373
00:22:09,244 --> 00:22:11,330
<i>There are still many people</i>
<i>trapped at La Playa Roja.</i>

374
00:22:11,413 --> 00:22:13,665
<i>Our faces are all over the news.</i>

375
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:15,959
[EMIL] <i>We can't lose focus.</i>
<i>We need to stick to the plan.</i>

376
00:22:16,043 --> 00:22:18,420
[LUCAS] <i>You owe us 50 million.</i>

377
00:22:18,503 --> 00:22:20,756
<i>I need to keep an eye on everyone.</i>

378
00:22:20,839 --> 00:22:24,176
<i>I won't let another innocent member</i>
<i>of our staff get hurt.</i>

379
00:22:24,259 --> 00:22:25,719
<i>I thought we'd never see each other again.</i>

380
00:22:25,802 --> 00:22:27,721
<i>- You're pretty impressive.</i>
<i>- You're even more so.</i>

381
00:22:27,804 --> 00:22:29,723
<i>You were able to bring them safely here.</i>

382
00:22:29,806 --> 00:22:32,142
<i>- So you're the traitor.</i>
<i>- Who are your accomplices?!</i>
